The article is a press briefing by Ben Rhodes and Dan Restrepo to preview President Obama's trip to the Summit of the Americas. The briefing discusses the importance of the Americas to the US in terms of economic growth and security. It also highlights the success of US engagement in the region and the increased respect for US leadership. The briefing outlines the President's schedule, including his speech at the Port of Tampa about the importance of US exports to the Americas, his participation in the CEO Summit of the Americas, and his meetings with other leaders of the Americas. The briefing also addresses various issues that will be discussed at the summit, including drug policy, labor conditions in Colombia, US relations with the Americas, and the potential participation of Cuba in the summit.